  "texts": [
    "We therefore developed an alternative approach, DeepScore, aiming for machine and setting independence, by estimating the magnitude of ΔF without its correction direction from a single image (Methods, see 19, 20).",
    "The intent was to create a slower yet machine-independent auto-focus algorithm, based on the directionless score and classical optimization (tested with the simplex method developed by Nelder and Mead 21).",
    "This algorithm can then be used to generate, with minimal manual input, a new training set in case of a required DeepFocus recalibration.",
    "We found that DeepScore, when used with classical optimization, can effectively infer a parameter set F that leads to sharp image formation, albeit, as expected, with slower convergence than the regular DeepFocus model (Supplementary Fig. 5, Supplementary Text 2).",
    "Using this approach, we generated a new, smaller training data set (n = 10 locations, 31% of the original training set) for a SEM where DeepFocus had diverged."
  ],
